PREMIUM ENVIRONMENT-FRIENDLY ZERO VOC PAINTS

EXTENDED LABOUR WARRANTY 
 
QUALIFIED PAINTERS
 
ON-TIME GUARANTEE
BEST PRICE GUARANTEE

A responsive management team should there be any challenges 
Detailed pricing that lets you know what you are getting for your money

Our customer service department will ask for some basic information about your project and will schedule one of our estimators to come out to discuss your project. We are a licensed and insured company that distinguishes our company from smaller and insecure businesses.

We strive to exceed your expectations and focus all of our energy and resources on delivering outstanding results.

profile:
Trying to remodel a bathroom by yourself? Forget the hassle and let the Bathroom Builders team efficiently install your bathroom to eliminate your stress.
The process starts with a fun and informative in-home consultation with your personal Bathroom Builders design consultant. We provide this service free of charge, so you have nothing to lose and everything to learn! Your design consultant will simplify the sometimes complex home renovation process by walking you through product selection and design.
When it’s time to start constructing your new bathroom, factory-trained Bathroom Builders installers will complete your project in as little as a few days, answering any questions along the way. Our professional installers will respect your family’s home. They’ll be on time, courteous and, most importantly, they’ll get the job done right the first time.
Bathroom Builders install both our own line of products and products from the best national brands. With countless colors, textures and styles to choose from, if you can dream it, we can likely make it happen. Learn more about our bathroom remodeling products: Explore our replacement bathtubs, walk-in bathtubs, bathtub to shower conversions, bathroom vanities, bathroom flooring and more.
Bathroom Builders are fully licensed and insured. Bathroom builders brand products carry a manufacturer's limited lifetime warranty against product defects. Financing is available. We proudly serve in all of the Greater Toronto Area including Mississauga, Oakville, Burlington, Hamilton, Toronto, Richmond Hill, and Vaughan

Owning a home is one of the most important financial and sentimental assets that one can have. Beyond building a financially reliable base, you want a home to match your lifestyle and your dreams. When you work with TK Contracting, you’re going to be getting a service that exceeds all expectations through our licensed and bonded tradespeople. 

Our Company
We at TK Contracting Inc.  Are passionate about the work we do. Our commitment is to work with our clients in order to achieve the best results in the project with a safe and timely manner.  We are dedicated to provide our clients with a high level of satisfaction. 

Heath and Safety Protocols
Our policy at TK Contracting is to maintain a safe working environment for everyone. Compliance with health and safety regulations are all outlined in the health and safety policy of TK Contracting.  Our employees are all trained yearly to follow these safety protocols. In order to reduce the risk of injuries at the workplace. 

COVID19 Precautions 
To keep our clients and workers safe, all workers will have a temperature check, and a log to record. All workers shall sanitize before Jobsite, and wear a mask during the entire day. TK Contracting makes sure every team member is tested before working. We are one of the few companies who follow these precautions.

Guaranteed Workmanship 
Our company ensures that each project is handled with good quality materials and professional knowledge to achieve the highest level of satisfaction. We provide a quality service on every project. TK Contracting offers a free written guarantee of 12 months from the date of completion.

profile:
Celebrating 25 Years in business!

​What We Do...
Residential & Commercial Interior & Exterior Re-Painting

What We Don't Do...
New Construction, Industrial, Faux Finishing, Wood Restoration, Paper Hanging.

Our Promise...
We're not jacks-of-all-trades...we specialize and focus on one thing, and do it "Sehr gut" (pronounced "zair goot") - German for "very good"!

"Meister Painters" (pronounced "My-sister"), means, as you may have guessed, "Master Painters". Along with being a nod to our heritage, we like to think it highlights the skill and commitment that our small family of local painters will bring to your painting project - something that our hundreds of satisfied customers will attest to. 

We are fully insured and price competitive; however, if you're shopping around for the cheapest price, then, in all honesty, we're probably not the painting contractor for you.

Our commitment is to give you full value for your dollar with excellent workmanship and products, friendliness and integrity, a timely, efficient process, and a happy, stress-free experience that will have you recommending us to your friends and having us back again in the future!

Our Service Area...
We service all areas of the Niagara and Hamilton regions, as listed below. It's a large geographical area, but whether you live around the corner or in the next town, our hard-working, local painters always go the extra mile to give you a great paint job! 

Niagara-on-the-Lake                         Hamilton
Niagara Falls                                    Ancaster
St. Catharines                                  Dundas
Fonthill                                            Stoney Creek
Vineland/Jordan                               Grimsby
Beamsville                                       Binbrook
Welland                                           Smithville
Port Colborne                                   Waterdown
Fort Erie                                          Burlington
   
Call or email us with any questions or to request a free quote!
 The Meister Method:

1) The Right Products...
- super-adhesion primers to ensure top-coat adhesion.
- siliconized, paintable caulk for superior elasticity and durability  
- low V.O.C. paints for a healthy living environment.
- washable matt finishes for that smooth, designer look that will stay looking great for years to come.
- elastomeric exterior coatings for unmatched durability and protection from the elements.

2) Thorough Preparation...
- washing, scraping, sanding, caulking, filling and priming -
  everything that is needed to make the top-coat look great and
  last.

3) Thorough Coverage...
- two standard coats, generously applied to ensure whole-surface
  saturation, a smooth, even finish, and proper protection.  

4) Clean Edges...
- clean, professional lines where different colours or surfaces meet.
- if we're painting the walls, but not the ceilings because they're in good shape and the previous painter did an improper edge, we'll just double-edge the ceiling line with white, flat paint to allow us to start fresh and create a new edge with the wall colour. This saves you money by not having to paint the whole ceiling!

5) Neat, Safe Worksites...
- everything is properly covered off, sites are cleaned up daily, and
  tools and equipment are kept organized and out of the way.
- Ladders are properly set up and braced and/or tied off; lift
​  operation areas roped off etc.
- We practice strict safety habits for our protection - and carry
  $2,000,000.00 liability insurance for yours!
products:
Paint Store Info...
Our main supplier is Dulux, although if you have a preference for other premium brands, such as Sherwin-Williams or Benjamin Moore, we're happy to accommodate. We've included a quick-reference list below for your convenience of all their stores in our service area, complete with address and telephone number.
  
Suggested Dulux lines...
Their top line is called Diamond, both for interior as well as exterior. Generally, we use Diamond Matt for walls; Diamond Semi-gloss for trim, doors, and cabinetry, and flat for ceilings. For the exterior Diamond line, we use semi-gloss for trim and doors, satin for siding, and flat for masonry & stucco.
